Mentor Zaheer Khan remains confident in the team's ability to bounce back, emphasizing the need to play good cricket and avoid relying on net run rate.
title: Explained: How Rishabh Pant's LSG can still qualify for IPL 2025 playoffs

description: Sanjana Ganesan expressed her dismay on Instagram regarding the online attention her son, Angad, is receiving. She and Jasprit Bumrah are working hard to protect him from social media's negative impacts. Sanjana emphasized that their presence at the cricket stadium was to support Jasprit, not to invite unwanted scrutiny and judgment towards their child, urging for more kindness online.
title: Our son is not a topic for your entertainment: Sanjana Ganesan

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, the Indian government banned 16 Pakistani YouTube channels, including prominent news outlets, for allegedly spreading misinformation and inciting communal discord. Shoaib Akhtar's cricket-focused YouTube channel was also blocked amidst concerns over content regulation during sensitive times. The ban reflects efforts to curb divisive narratives, though Akhtar's content was primarily apolitical.
title: Pahalgam Terror Attack: Shoaib Akhtar's YouTube channel banned in India

description: The Indian government has banned 16 Pakistani YouTube channels for allegedly spreading misinformation and communally sensitive content. This action follows diplomatic measures against Pakistan, including visa suspensions and the halting of the Indus Waters Treaty, in response to the Pahalgam terror attack. Pakistan has denied involvement in the attack, calling for an independent investigation.
title: 'Provocative, communal content': Govt bans 16 Pakistan YouTube channels

description: Rishabh Pant, the Lucknow Super Giants captain, is facing criticism for his poor batting form in the IPL, scoring only 110 runs in 10 matches with six single-digit scores. Despite being the most expensive player in IPL auction history, his performance hasn't met expectations.
title: Rishabh Pant defends his poor form: 'It's not the right thing to do...'
Trump’s border chief says 'no US citizen was deported' after 2-year-old sent to Honduras
Watch: Scottish leader Anas Sarwar asks Pakistanis to 'take power'

description: BJP MP Nishikant Dubey has alleged a new form of Pakistani terrorism, claiming over five lakh Pakistani women have entered India through marriage but haven't received citizenship. This follows the government's visa restrictions on Pakistani citizens after a deadly terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir's Pahalgam, which killed 26 people.
title: BJP MP Nishikant Dubey raises concerns over 'new face of Pakistani terrorism' amid Pahalgam attack fallout

description: Gold prices experienced significant volatility, initially soaring to record highs due to safe-haven demand amid geopolitical and economic uncertainties last week. However, prices corrected sharply following signals of potential trade negotiations and peace efforts. Investors are closely monitoring central bank independence, inflation expectations, and U.S. economic data for future policy direction.
title: Gold price prediction: What's gold rate outlook for this week

description: The government has formally protested BBC's use of "militants" instead of "terrorists" in its coverage of the Pahalgam attack, which resulted in 26 deaths. Simultaneously, India banned 16 Pakistani YouTube channels, including prominent networks like Dawn News and Geo News, for allegedly spreading misinformation and provocative content against India, its army, and security agencies following the tragic incident.
title: J&K attack: Govt writes to BBC over its report terming 'terrorists' as 'militants'

description: Following the tragic Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26 tourists, the Jammu and Kashmir Legislative Assembly convened a special session today. India banned 16 Pakistani YouTube channels, including prominent news outlets, for disseminating misinformation against the nation and its security forces.
title: Pahalgam terror attack: J&K assembly holds special session - Top developments

description: A Tesla Cybertruck owner in California tested Elon Musk's claims about water capabilities. The owner activated 'Wade Mode' to cross water. Unfortunately, the Cybertruck got stuck, needing help from California Highway Patrol. Musk had suggested it could handle rivers, but the warranty advises caution. This incident shows the importance of understanding a vehicle's limits, despite marketing claims.
title: Tesla Cybertruck owner gets stuck in water after believing Elon Musk’s claims
Who is Kai-Ji Adam Lo? Suspect named in Vancouver car attack

description: Amid escalating tensions, AIMIM leader Asaduddin Owaisi strongly criticized Pakistan, citing ceasefire violations and rhetoric following the Pahalgam terror attack. He asserted Pakistan lags behind India, both economically and strategically.
title: 'You are not just half an hour, but half a century behind': Owaisi mocks Pakistan

description: Actress Navina Bole, known for her roles in 'Ishqbaaz' and 'Mile Jab Hum Tum,' has accused filmmaker Sajid Khan of inappropriate behavior. In an interview, Bole revealed that Khan allegedly invited her to his home and asked her to "take off her clothes." She recounted feeling deeply uncomfortable during the encounter, which occurred in the mid-2000s.
title: Actress Navina Bole makes shocking accusations about Sajid Khan

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, BSE Sensex and Nifty50, opened in green on Monday. While BSE Sensex went above 79,600, Nifty50 crossed 24,150.
title: BSE Sensex over 300 points up; Nifty50 above 24,100

description: Canadians are heading to the polls in a crucial federal election, triggered by political shifts and trade tensions with the US. Prime Minister Mark Carney faces challenges from Conservative leader Pierre Poilievre and NDP's Jagmeet Singh. Key issues include affordability for younger voters and healthcare for older Canadians, as parties vie for a majority in the House of Commons.
title: Canada elections 2025: Key candidates, major parties, issues

description: Robert Vadra, businessman and husband of Congress MP Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, has clarified his earlier remark regarding the Pahalgam terrorist attack. In a Facebook post, Vadra condemned the attack, calling it an "attack on the soul of humanity." He emphasized his solidarity with India and stated that no justification exists for violence against innocent people.
title: 'Intentions misinterpreted': Robert Vadra clarifies remark on Pahalgam attack

description: Shahid Afridi has strongly condemned the Indian government and army following the recent terrorist attack in Pahalgam, questioning the response time of Indian forces. He accused India of carrying out acts of terrorism and falsely blaming Pakistan, emphasizing that neither Islam nor Pakistan supports such violence.
title: 'Islam teaches us peace': Shahid Afridi says India kill its own people
Mass casualty reported as boat collides in Florida, authorities hunt fleeing vessel

description: Tensions escalate along the LoC as Pakistan violates the ceasefire for the fourth consecutive night, prompting a strong response from India. Following the Pahalgam terror attack, over 500 Pakistani nationals have exited India after visa revocations. Meanwhile, US President Trump urges Putin to pursue peace talks with Ukraine amidst ongoing conflict and missile strikes.
title: Morning news wrap: Pak violates ceasefire again, 509 Pak nationals leave India & more

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, the United States has called on India and Pakistan to find a responsible solution. The US is closely monitoring the situation and has been in contact with both governments. Prime Minister Narendra Modi expressed grief over the attack, which targeted tourists. The attack, the deadliest in the Valley since the 2019 Pulwama strike, targeted mostly tourists and was claimed by The Resistance Front (TRF), a proxy of the Pakistan-based terrorist organisation Lashkar-e-Taiba (LeT).
title: Pahalgam terror attack: US calls for 'responsible solution' amid India-Pak tensions

description: The Supreme Court of India is scheduled to hear a petition advocating for a ban on sexually explicit content on OTT platforms and social media. Petitioners urge the establishment of a National Content Control Authority to regulate online pornography, citing concerns about its impact on youth, societal values, and public safety.
title: Supreme Court to hear plea seeking ban on explicit content on OTT platforms

description: Virat Kohli playfully mocked KL Rahul's 'this is my ground' Kantara celebration after Royal Challengers Bengaluru defeated Delhi Capitals. This was in response to Rahul's earlier celebration at Chinnaswamy Stadium after guiding Delhi to victory against RCB. Krunal Pandya's unbeaten 73 and Kohli's 51 helped RCB chase down the target of 162.
title: 'This is my ground': Virat Kohli recreates Kantara scene to tease KL Rahul
Massive immigration raid: US Police smash nightclub window to arrest 100+; Trump celebrates

description: Pakistani troops have violated the ceasefire along the Line of Control for the fourth consecutive night, initiating unprovoked firing in the Poonch and Kupwara districts of Jammu and Kashmir, according to Indian Army officials. This escalation follows a recent terror attack in Pahalgam, where 26 Hindu tourists were killed.
title: Pakistan violates ceasefire for fourth consecutive night, India responds

description: Donald Trump has expressed his disappointment with Vladimir Putin, urging him to cease hostilities in Ukraine and finalize a peace agreement. Following a meeting with Volodymyr Zelenskyy, Trump criticized Putin's attacks on civilian areas, suggesting a potential shift in strategy towards Russia. Efforts to broker a deal continue, with the US proposing a controversial plan involving recognition of Russian-occupied territories.
title: 'Stop shooting and sign a deal': Trump to Putin after meeting Zelenskyy

description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal Financial Services recommends ICICI Bank and 360 One WAM as top stock picks for the week starting April 28, 2025. ICICI Bank's Q4 performance showcased robust growth. 360 ONE reported record PAT, fueled by recurring revenue growth.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for the week starting today

description: Congress leader Udit Raj criticised Shashi Tharoor's remarks on the Pahalgam terror attack, questioning his allegiance to the party and suggesting he was acting as a BJP spokesperson. Raj challenged Tharoor's comparison of the attack to the intelligence failure in Israel during the Hamas strike. He further inquired about Tharoor's knowledge of terror attacks in America post-9/11.
title: Udit Raj slams Tharoor over Pahalgam remarks: Trying to be a super-BJP man?

description: During a match against Delhi Capitals, Virat Kohli was seen in a heated argument with KL Rahul, though the reason remained unclear. Kohli's fifty, along with Krunal Pandya's unbeaten 73, propelled Royal Challengers Bengaluru to a six-wicket victory, securing their top position in the IPL table.
title: Virat Kohli and KL Rahul exchange words during DC vs RCB match

description: Ravi Bishnoi's unexpected sixes and Jasprit Bumrah's milestone weren't enough as Mumbai Indians defeated Lucknow Super Giants by 54 runs. Bumrah's impressive 4 for 22 not only secured the win but also made him the highest wicket-taker for Mumbai Indians in IPL history, surpassing Lasith Malinga. Mumbai's victory was fueled by strong batting performances from Ryan Rickelton and Suryakumar Yadav.
title: Watch: Ravi Bishnoi celebrates after smashing Jasprit Bumrah for a six

description: Brokerage firms offer varied outlooks on Indian companies. Morgan Stanley remains positive on Axis Bank despite muted earnings, while Jefferies highlights SBI Life's strong new business growth. Goldman Sachs sees improvement for SBI Cards, but Citigroup is cautious on Tech Mahindra due to high expectations. HSBC suggests reducing Rallis India due to missed estimates and pricing pressures.
title: Axis Bank, Tech Mahindra & more: Top stocks on brokers' radar today

description: KL Rahul, after a stellar performance in ODIs, including the 2023 World Cup and Champions Trophy, aims to reclaim his spot in India's T20I squad for the 2026 T20 World Cup. Despite being overlooked for the recent T20 World Cup, his current form in the IPL 2025, where he is the leading run-scorer for Delhi Capitals, is promising.
title: Kevin Pietersen: 'I back KL Rahul to bat at No. 4 for India in T20 cricket'
Meta AI under fire after bots engage in disturbing conversations with kids: Report
Titanic survivor's haunting letter sells for £300,000: Here's what it said

description: In Tamil Nadu, two ministers, V Senthil Balaji and K Ponmudy, resigned from the cabinet. Governor R N Ravi accepted their resignations following Chief Minister M K Stalin's recommendation. S Muthusamy takes over Balaji's portfolios. S S Sivasankar and R S Rajakannappan get additional charges. T Manothangaraj was re-inducted into the cabinet. The swearing-in ceremony is scheduled for Monday.
title: DMK forces ministers Balaji and Ponmudy, facing court fire, to quit

description: Sunny Deol's 'Jaat,' also starring Randeep Hooda, continues its strong performance at the box office, nearing Rs 90 crore after 18 days. Despite competition from Akshay Kumar's 'Kesar 2' and Emraan Hashmi’s ‘Ground Zero,’ 'Jaat' saw a rise in collections over the weekend, with Sunday marking its highest earning day in the third week.
title: ‘Jaat’ Box Office Day 18: Sunny Deol’s film stays strong; inches towards Rs 90cr

description: Agra police have apprehended Manoj Chaudhary, who claimed to be a 'gau rakshak' and member of Kshatriya Gau Raksha Dal, for allegedly murdering a biryani seller. Chaudhary initially asserted the killing was retaliation for the Pahalgam attack, a claim police dismissed. Authorities believe the crime stemmed from a dispute over the biryani's quality, not vigilantism.
title: Man who 'shot UP biryani seller over Pahalgam' held

description: Goa CM Pramod Sawant predicted the potential split of Pakistan due to Balochistan's independence push, assuring BJP workers of PM Modi's retaliation for the Pahalgam attack. He contrasted India's growing Muslim population and secular harmony with Pakistan's insularity.
title: Pakistan on verge of split, Balochistan will be a new nation: Goa CM

description: Chia seeds have surged in popularity as a superfood, lauded for their nutritional benefits. However, consuming them dry poses risks, as highlighted by Dr. Salhab, potentially leading to esophageal blockages requiring surgery. Soaking chia seeds is crucial; it aids digestion, prevents discomfort, and enhances nutrient absorption, unlocking their full potential for optimal health benefits.
title: US doctor warns that eating chia seeds like this can land you in the hospital
Who is Tejpaul Bhatia? Indian-origin executive takes over as Axiom Space CEO

description: D.C.'s interim Attorney, Ed Martin, is challenging the Wikimedia Foundation's nonprofit status, alleging that Wikipedia allows foreign actors to spread propaganda and manipulate information, potentially violating its tax-exempt obligations. Martin's concerns include biased edits related to the Israel-Hamas conflict and the prioritization of Wikipedia in search results, demanding the Foundation to address these issues by May 15th.
title: US attorney sends warning letter, says ‘Wikipedia breaking law about ... '

description: Rajasthan BJP chief Madan Rathore rebuked MLA Balmukundacharya for raising slogans and displaying posters inside Jaipur's Jama Masjid, which incited tensions. Rathore emphasized that such actions contradict the party's principles and instructed members to maintain communal harmony. Balmukundacharya has apologized, and Rathore has urged all representatives to prioritize peace and public sentiment.
title: BJP rebukes MLA for provoking unrest

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi has vowed to punish those behind the Pahalgam attack, emphasizing the unity of 1.4 billion Indians as a powerful force against terrorism. He assured justice for the victims' families, promising a strong response to the perpetrators and their supporters.
title: Blood boiling but national unity will steer Pahalgam response: PM Modi

description: RBI Governor Sanjay Malhotra affirmed India's commitment to market reforms despite global protectionism, highlighting liberalisation in key sectors and near-total FDI automatic route. He projected India as a dynamic powerhouse, crediting monetary policy for taming inflation with recent rate cuts. India's economy demonstrates resilience with strong growth, aiming to be a developed nation by 2047.
title: India committed to reforms: RBI governor

description: Class VII NCERT social science textbooks have removed references to the Mughals and Delhi Sultanate, replaced with chapters on ancient Indian dynasties and "sacred geography." The revisions, aligning with NEP 2020, aim to incorporate Indian traditions and philosophies, featuring Indian writers and themes in English textbooks while also highlighting government initiatives and constitutional rights.
title: Indian rulers in, Mughals out of Std 7 textbooks

description: Geopolitical tensions between India and Pakistan, triggered by the Pahalgam terror attack, are casting a shadow over Dalal Street. Market sentiment will also be influenced by foreign fund trading patterns, quarterly earnings from Indian and US companies, and overall trends in US markets.
title: India-Pakistan tension, FPIs to decide trend on D-Street

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, India revoked most visas for Pakistani citizens, leading to 509 Pakistani nationals exiting via Attari. Simultaneously, 744 Indian nationals returned from Pakistan through Wagah. The revocation, part of a diplomatic response, set deadlines for various visa categories, with states instructed to ensure compliance and address overstays under the Immigration and Foreigners Act.
title: Pahalgam attack aftermath: Deadline over, 509 Pak nationals leave via Attari
